OL,5,CCongo
OL,7,FA British man is among the 37 people
OL,8,Fwho have been sentenced to death in
OL,9,FCongo after being convicted on charges
OL,10,Fof participating in a coup attempt.
OL,12,FThe defendants, most of them Congolese
OL,13,Fbut also including three Americans, a
OL,14,FBelgian and a Canadian, have five days
OL,15,Fto appeal the verdict on charges that
OL,16,Finclude attempted coup, terrorism and
OL,17,Fcriminal association. Fourteen people
OL,18,Fwere acquitted in the trial, which
OL,19,Fopened in June.
